<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="105.[189,457,904,930]" box="[189,457,904,930]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,904,930]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,904,930]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[189,1399,952,1164]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[311,676,952,978]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[311,676,952,978]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[683,772,952,978]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[826,1009,952,979]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collicola" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[826,1009,952,979]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">S. (A.) collicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1014,1104,952,978]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Except for the characters given in the key, the species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[771,916,989,1016]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[771,916,989,1016]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">S. (A.) bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[923,1013,989,1015]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having the male superior lobe on both sides wider (higher) than long instead of longer than wide; and from 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[1112,1299,1026,1054]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collicola" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[1112,1299,1026,1054]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">S. (A.) collicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1307,1399,1026,1052]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having the more posterior one of the ventral tooth-like projections on the right superior lobe lateral instead of marginal and by having the respective projection on the left side superior lobe large and sharp instead of small and rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="105.[189,324,1205,1231]" box="[189,324,1205,1231]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1205,1231]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1205,1231]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[189,1399,1254,1354]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[425,533,1255,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inventum">
<emphasis box="[425,533,1255,1280]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">inventum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of the Latin words ‘ 
<emphasis box="[924,1039,1255,1280]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">in ventum</emphasis>
’, meaning ‘under the wind’. It is a translation of the informal Malayan name of 
<collectingRegion box="[763,838,1291,1317]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Sabah</collectingRegion>
, ‘ 
<emphasis box="[859,1131,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Negeri Di Bawah Bayu</emphasis>
’, meaning ‘land under the wind’ and referring to the 
<typeStatus box="[539,590,1328,1354]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
locality of the species. The name is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
